# Form controls and iOS input zoom (React Native / Expo)

On **iOS Safari** (and in some WebViews), focusing a text field whose effective size reads as **smaller than ~16px** can trigger **viewport zoom** in hybrid contexts. In **pure React Native** `TextInput`, use explicit typography so fields never ship at tiny default sizes.

## Requirements

1. **Components**: Prefer **`fontSize: 16`** (or `text-base` / design tokens that resolve to **≥16**) on the **`TextInput`** (and multiline fields), not only on labels. Avoid `text-xs` / `text-sm` equivalents on those nodes for primary flows.

2. **Do not** “fix” zoom by locking the WebView or web shell to `user-scalable=no` or `maximum-scale=1`; that hurts accessibility.

3. **Exceptions**: Decorative or non-text inputs (`checkbox`, `switch`, etc.) are not the focus of this rule.

When adding new text fields, verify on iPhone that focus does not cause unexpected zoom if the screen is ever embedded in a web view.
